text: Tachibana: "Sit-ups and standing long jump!"
Standing long jump: 171.40 cm
Tachibana: "Next up is the standing long jump."
Chibi Bana: "Yeah, but honestly, I'm already wiped out from the shuttle run."
You: "Right? Usually these fitness tests are split across a few days. I’m already dead, man."
Tachibana: "What are you saying? We’re just getting started!"
Tachibana: "By the way, the world record for the standing long jump is...
373 cm
Tachibana: "Let’s aim for that!"
You: "Yeah right, like you could get anywhere near that."
Chibi Bana: "Exactly, Sis. Sorry, but for you it’s better to compare with the world’s lowest records."
Tachibana: "Why am I getting roasted before I’ve even started... What did I do to deserve this..."
Tachibana: "Alright! I’ll go first!"
Tachibana: "Here I go!"
Tachibana: "50 cm"
You: "Isn’t that like the average height of a newborn?"
Chibi: "Yeah, pretty much 50 cm... Still, your form is perfect as always."
You: "Right... She looks like she could jump way further, but in reality, it's just not happening."
Chibi: "By the way...
Chibi: "Three roll cakes lined up (each 15-20 cm) is already impossible."
Umbrella: about 50-55 cm. Some types, nope, can't clear it.
iPhone 14 Pro Max (vertical): about 16 cm. That’s a jump of about three iPhones.
Three sandals: about 50 cm. Losing to three sandals, that’s rough.
Chibi: "If Sis had a 50 cm wide cliff in front and a wild tiger behind, that's just guaranteed death. She'd either offer her head or just fall off, no way out."
You: "Comparing Tachibana's jump to everyday things really highlights how lame it is."
Chibi: "Yeah. Honestly, not even beating a newborn is the funniest part. How low can you go?"
Chibi: "It’s like a life that just can’t catch a break."
You: "Alright! Chibi, you’re up next!"
You: "She’s actually pretty positive, huh…"
Chibi: "Yeah... I guess it’s good I’m the optimistic type..."
Chibi: "Alright, it’s my turn."
Chibi: "Here goes!"
You: "What?!"
Tachibana: "Is she... flying? In the sky?"
Record: 330 cm
Chibi: "Hmm, guess I’m just off today."
You: "That looked like a poster for The Girl Who Leapt Through Time."
Tachibana: "She was soaring... The sky felt closer than the ground."
Chibi: "Don’t make such a big deal out of it... It’s not that amazing a record."
Tachibana: "No, don’t be modest! I actually remember some famous people’s records."

Tachibana: "Koji Murofushi (Olympic gold hammer throw, former Japan rep)
In high school, he jumped 327 cm."
Arne Tvervaag: 371 cm, official world record holder (all-time best)
Byron Jones: 373 cm, best ever at NFL Combine
Tachibana: "So honestly, it makes more sense to compare Chibi’s record to the world’s top athletes."
You: "No way... She’s almost up there with Japan’s and the world’s superheroes…"
Tachibana: "Exactly. So please, don’t downplay it. If you do, what does that make my record?"
Chibi: "...You’re right..."
You: "Guess I’ll just have to crawl behind the newborns... dragging my head..."
Results
Tachibana: 50 cm
You: 230 cm
Chibi: 330 cm
Chibi: "Last up... sit-ups."
You: "Yeah..."
You: "But honestly, isn't this one really for us...?"
You: "Isn't this really for Tachibana's sake?"
Chibi: "Yeah, probably..."
Chibi: "Sis, every time you try to do sit-ups you just roll over and pass out."
Chibi: "How weak are your abs, seriously."
Chibi: "But the real reason you wanted to save sit-ups for last is to show us how much you've improved, right?"
Tachibana: "Yeah..."
Chibi: "We'll watch you. You'll be fine."
You: "Yeah, really, it doesn't matter if you can't do it. Just give it a shot and have fun."
Tachibana: "Okay... got it! Watch me!"
Both: "..."
Tachibana: "..."
You: "What's with this dramatic cut-in?"
Chibi: "That's some intense energy... All this just for sit-ups?"
Tachibana: "Hmph!"
Both: "..."
Tachibana: "!!"
You: "Whoa!"
Chibi: "You did it, Sis!"
Tachibana: "...Huff, huff..."
Tachibana: "No more... I can't get up..."
You: "Your abs are way too weak..."
Chibi: "Come on, the shuttle run was way harder than this!"
You: "But that was awesome! You did it!"
Chibi: "Yeah! The sit-up project we've been doing for months... We finally made it!"
Tachibana: "But... after all that, I only managed to do one... I'm happy, but it feels complicated..."
Tachibana: "Still, just once, huh..."
You: "First there was a second, so there could be a minute. A minute led to an hour."
You: "An hour led to a day, a day to a month, and then a year."
You: "You can only do it once? No, you managed to do it once. That one time could lead to something big."
You: "That one sit-up might bring a hundred more in the future."
You: "Honestly, I don't even need to tell you this. You've already accomplished way more amazing things. You know how incredible that first step really is."

Chibi: "Yeah, Sis. And let me say, there's no need to give up just because you have no talent. If you want to do it, if you want to get good, you just keep at it. I learned that from you today. Thanks."
Tachibana: "Yeah... Thank you too."
Tachibana: "You know... today was a really good day."
You: "Yeah. But my body's shot. My shoulders, back, and neck all hurt."
Chibi: "You’re basically an old man. You're getting closer to death every day."
Chibi: "So, when's your funeral?"
You: "Too soon! I just said my body hurts!"
You: "You jump straight to death way too fast!"
Tachibana: "..."
Tachibana: "Thank you for everything. I only made it this far because you were here. Because you were here, I’ve had so much fun living."
Tachibana: "We fought over silly things, cried over tough times."
Tachibana: "Even so, I’ll never forget the days I spent with you..."
Tachibana: "Thank you... really. Watch over me from heaven, okay?"
Tachibana: "Watch over us."
You: "I’m not dead yet!"
